<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920113-0129</DOCNO><DOCID>920113-0129.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- Recognition Equipment Inc.:   Letter of Intent Is Signed   For $39 Million Acquisition</HL><DATE>01/13/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   REC TT</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)OFFICE EQUIPMENT (OFF)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH CAROLINA (NC)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Recognition Equipment Inc., Dallas, said it signed aletter of intent to purchase assets of a unit of LosAngeles-based TransTechnology Corp. for $39 million.   Recognition Equipment said the proposed purchase is forthe document processing and financial management systemsbusiness of Lundy Financial Systems of Charlotte, N.C. Thedivision of TransTechnology, a maker of industrial andaerospace products, has annual revenue of approximately $45million and sells its hardware and software primarily tobanks, utilities and insurance firms.</LP><TEXT>   Recognition Equipment, which makes image anddata-processing equipment and software, said it would pay forthe assets primarily in cash. Closing of the transaction isexpected in March, the company said. It said the proposedtransaction is subject to completion of a definitiveagreement and board approval by both companies.   Recognition Equipment stated the proposed acquisitionwould give it the opportunity to &quot;significantly expand&quot; itspresence in automated work processing.</TEXT></DOC>